  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba \u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4 \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0db8\u0d9c\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0daf\u0dbb\u0dcf \u0d9c\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db6\u0dd0\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dd4",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Passengers could not afford the increase in train fares",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is said that the railway department has revised the fares which cannot be afforded by the passengers and the passengers coming to Colombo for work from distant provinces cannot bear the increase in the railway transport fares.",
        "They also said that although some increase in train fares was expected due to the increase in fuel prices, this unusual increase was a decision taken by the administration and the relevant minister without any concern for the passengers.",
        "He said that by increasing the fares of the railway service, which is mostly used by the poor passengers for their travel activities, by asking what kind of profits the government expects, this will have a severe impact on the family economy of the passengers who come to Colombo from far away every day.",
        "They said that having a governing authority on the train that does not understand the injustice of revising the fares of the common people's most valuable public transport service, which has caused a crisis and the travel fees of the ministers, which has plunged the country into the abyss and created a crisis, is a matter that should be brought to the attention of the new president.",
        "In this regard, we also asked the General Secretary of the Railway Station Master's Association, Mr. Kasun Chamara Jayasekara, and he said that his association does not approve of the tariff revision, which has been maintained as a service since the past, so that the railway passenger transport service is no longer a service.",
        "He said that even though some increase was expected compared to the increase in fuel prices, his union also accepts that this revision of the fares, which has been done in a way that inconveniences the passengers, cannot be tolerated.",
        "Stating that every time the railway department tried to increase the fares in the past, his union worked to ensure that my people were not affected.",
        "He said that no one thought that the fees would rise to such an extent.",
        "He said that even though an idea was raised that the fares should be revised, they did not expect such an increase, but the passengers also complained to their union.",
        "He further said that he hopes to take some relief measures for the passengers by explaining the facts to the government about this unfair fare revision.",
        "We also asked the General Superintendent of Railways Mr. Dhammika Jayasundara regarding the increase in the railway transport charges and he said that if the public transport service is to be continued as a service without being a burden to the country, the fare revision will have to be done in this way.",
        "He mentioned that the previous daily fuel cost was 10 million rupees and said that the cost has now increased to 45 million rupees.",
        "Stating that the current fuel cost shows an increase of 35 million rupees compared to the previous fuel cost, he said that the passenger fares have also been revised in order to reduce the loss caused by the increased cost.",
        "He said that if there is a drop in fuel charges, it is hoped that the benefit will be given to the passengers.",
        "He further said that for the convenience of the passengers, night train services have been started in Jaffna and Beliatta, and the services up to Trincomalee are also to be started."
      ],
